                            <comment id="13784933" author="nkeywal" created="Thu, 3 Oct 2013 09:00:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks for the review Nick &amp;amp; Elliott.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any recommendations on setting new values and why?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It depends on a lot of factors, but with the 0.96 there is no detection time when we kill -9 a server, so we should have a full recovery in less than 30s. Then if we&apos;re a little bit aggressive we can say that the cluster is not overloaded and try something like 15s.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
